                  <Text layoutX="52.0" layoutY="208.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Computer programming is the process of designing and writing instructions that a computer can follow to perform tasks. These instructions, written in programming languages, form what we call a program. Programming is the foundation of all software applications—from mobile apps and websites to games and complex operating systems. Understanding how to program equips you with the skills to solve problems using logic and code.In today’s digital world, programming plays a vital role in every industry—from healthcare and education to finance and entertainment. It powers automation, enables data analysis, and facilitates communication through digital platforms. Learning how to program not only opens up a wide range of career opportunities but also helps develop computational thinking—an essential skill that enhances logical reasoning and creativity.Moreover, programming allows individuals to create tools and applications that solve real-world problems. Whether it’s developing a mobile app to help manage daily tasks or designing a website for a local business, programming empowers users to innovate and make an impact. As technology continues to evolve, the demand for skilled programmers continues to grow, making it a valuable and future-proof skill to learn." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
