                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="52.0" layoutY="1157.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Before writing actual code, it’s important to plan your solution using algorithms and flowcharts. An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure to solve a problem, while a flowchart is a visual representation of this process. These tools help programmers organize their thoughts and identify potential problems early in the development process." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
